3 Sec. 7. K.S.A. 65-2837 is hereby amended to read as follows: 65-
4 2837. As used in K.S.A. 65-2836, and amendments thereto, and in this
5 section:
6 (a) "Professional incompetency" means:
7 (1) One or more instances involving failure to adhere to the
8 applicable standard of care to a degree that constitutes gross negligence, as
9 determined by the board.
10 (2) Repeated instances involving failure to adhere to the applicable
11 standard of care to a degree that constitutes ordinary negligence, as
12 determined by the board.
13 (3) A pattern of practice or other behavior that demonstrates a
14 manifest incapacity or incompetence to practice the healing arts.
15 (b) "Unprofessional conduct" means:
16 (1) Solicitation of professional patronage through the use of
17 fraudulent or false advertisements, or profiting by the acts of those
18 representing themselves to be agents of the licensee.
19 (2) Representing to a patient that a manifestly incurable disease,
20 condition or injury can be permanently cured.
21 (3) Assisting in the care or treatment of a patient without the consent
22 of the patient, the attending physician or the patient's legal representatives.
23 (4) The use of any letters, words or terms as an affix, on stationery, in
24 advertisements or otherwise indicating that such person is entitled to
25 practice a branch of the healing arts for which such person is not licensed.
26 (5) Performing, procuring or aiding and abetting in the performance
27 or procurement of a criminal abortion.
28 (6) Willful betrayal of confidential information.
29 (7) Advertising professional superiority or the performance of
30 professional services in a superior manner.
31 (8) Advertising to guarantee any professional service or to perform
32 any operation painlessly.
33 (9) Participating in any action as a staff member of a medical care
34 facility that is designed to exclude or that results in the exclusion of any
35 person licensed to practice medicine and surgery from the medical staff of
36 a nonprofit medical care facility licensed in this state because of the
37 branch of the healing arts practiced by such person or without just cause.
38 (10) Failure to effectuate the declaration of a qualified patient as
